<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1555,1834]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,361,1735,1761]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">Identification</emphasis>
. This species was identified using the keys, descriptions, and illustrations by 
<bibRefCitation author="Blahnik, R. J." box="[1234,1409,1735,1761]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" pagination="1 - 318" refId="ref4978" refString="Blahnik, R. J. (1998) A revision of the Neotropical species of the genus Chimarra, subgenus Chimarra (Trichoptera: Philopotamidae). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 59, vi + 1 - 318." type="journal article" year="1998">Blahnik (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. It resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Denning 1941" authorityName="Denning" authorityYear="1941" box="[269,540,1771,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Philopotamidae" genus="Chimarra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pylaea">
<emphasis box="[269,376,1771,1798]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="583">C. pylaea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Denning, D. G." box="[381,540,1771,1797]" pageId="5" pageNumber="583" pagination="82 - 85" refId="ref5334" refString="Denning, D. G. (1941) Descriptions of three new species of Mexican Chimarrha (Trichoptera: Philopotamidae). Entomological News, 52, 82 - 85." type="journal article" year="1941">Denning 1941</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
most closely, with both having fold-like lateral lobes of tergum X. It differs from this species in having a less elongate ventral apex of each inferior appendage.
</paragraph>
